mobileOG_000727254|NA:Keyword|WP_162730883.1|stability/transfer/defense|NA|Plasmid Mrr_cat,Mrr_cat_2 Necessary for efficient RNA polymerase transcription elongation past template-encoded arresting sites. The arresting sites in DNA have the property of trapping a certain fraction of elongating RNA polymerases that pass through, resulting in locked ternary complexes.
